==English==
===Etymology===
Greek [[ελυτρον]] ‘sheath’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'ɛlɪtɹɒn/

===Noun===
'''elytron''' (''plural'' '''elytra''')
# a [[sheath]] or outer covering, especially around the spinal cord or over the hindwings of certain insects
#:*'''1997''': In a corner, the Darkling Beetle rustles in its Cage, its '''Elytra''' the same unforgiving white as the great sand-waste call’d ‘Kalahari’ lying north of here — Thomas Pynchon, ''Mason & Dixon''